article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 60, Towson 57
article.story: MIAMI, Ohio -- Allen Roberts scored a career-high 20 points and Julian Mavunga registered a double-double as Miami (Ohio) beat Towson 60-57 Friday night in the season opener for both teams. Mavunga had 14 points, including 7 of 9 free throw attempts, and had 14 rebounds. Twelve of Mavunga's points came in the second half. The win avenged an 82-71 loss to Towson in last season's opening game. Miami built a seven-point lead in the first half but neither team led by more than four points in the second half. The game was tied eight times, including 51-51 with 4:18 remaining. Two free throws by Mavunga with 3:50 to play put the RedHawks up for good at 53-51 and started a 5-0 run. Towson had a chance to tie the game but a 3-pointer by Troy Franklin with 11 seconds to go was off the mark. Isaiah Philmore led Towson with 12 points and Braxton Dupree added 11.
